	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you've ever used a SuperCard or M3 adapter on a Game Boy Advance or Nintendo DS, or if you've ever used a Famicom Disk System, the same thing is going on in a RAM based NES cart.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
